Software Requirement Types

Software requirements are the foundation of any software development project.  at the software should do.    
1. Functional Requirements 
     what the software should do
    Specify the functionality, features, and behaviors of the system
   
2. Non-Functional Requirements 
     how the software should behave
     Specify quality attributes, constraints, and performance expectations
    
3. User Requirements
      the needs and expectations of the users
    Specify the tasks users want to accomplish with the software
    
4. System Requirements
     overall system architecture and components
    Specify hardware, software, and infrastructure requirements
   
5. Business Requirements
     the business goals and objectives
    Specify the business rules, processes, and regulations

6. Technical Requirements 
     the technical constraints and specifications
     programming languages, frameworks, and tools
   
7. Interface Requirements
  the interactions between systems or components
    Specify APIs, data formats, and communication protocols
    
